<div class="description">
    <h3>Description</h3>

    <div class="body">
        <p>When doing digest authentification with different realms, the adpater does not check if the user supplied realm matches the configured one. So if one has authenticated once with a realm, the browser will send that realm along with the credentials. This validates just fine (real, username and pass are valid), which is a bug, as the realm does not match the configured one.</p>

<p>Bruce Lohr has supplied a working patch on the fw-general mailing list.</p>

